            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@justinmk I'm not sure what you mean by \"error trace\". I'd be grad to provide the info you need.\n\nI'll just try to describe the error from top to bottom here. Logs (`nvim -V10nvim-error.log`): [nvim-error.log](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/27013744/nvim-error.log)\n\n- I open the file locally: https://github.com/IlyasYOY/monotask/blob/f0c87ad90dcfca25bcc1e9653f5e7654b8a6f4e0/internal/pkg/version/version.go#L48-L53\n- I execute gopls' refactoring action (more on that here https://github.com/golang/go/issues/78920)\n- after that I get fzf-lua handler logic for vim.ui.select.\n- after I applied the action I get incorrect go code.\n- when I do the same refactoring using gopls without fzf-lua (before fix we merged in https://github.com/ibhagwan/fzf-lua/issues/2701) the code works fine.\n\nThe fzf-lua calls `vim.lsp.util.apply_text_edits` to create preview and we get the error after the application of those edits. Copying edits before passing them into the `vim.lsp.util.apply_text_edits` for making preview solves the issue.\n\n---\n\nI added print here: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua#L319\n\nAfter that I get two different edits. Here are the prints: [messages.txt](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/27014403/messages.txt)\n\n---\n\nHope this helps!",
